n&gt; different from yourself, will you attain the=\r\n state of fearlessness=E2=80=9D. Then\n&gt; the Lord taught him the path of Sel=\r\nf-enquiry. When Prahlada followed the\n&gt; Lord=E2=80=99s instructions and rea=\r\nlized Self, he attained the state of\n&gt; fearlessness.\n&gt; \n&gt; This story thus i=\r\nllustrates that even God cannot serve as permanent refuge\n&gt; from fear so lo=\r\nng as one retains the sense of difference [bheda-buddhi].\n&gt; Only by attaini=\r\nng the non-dual Self can one become truly and permanently\n&gt; free from fear.=\r\n\n&gt; \n&gt; Source: GURU VACHAKA KOVAI The Light of Supreme Truth or THE COLLECTI=\r\nON OF\n&gt; GURU=E2=80=99S SAYINGS translated from original Tamil By Sadhu Om a=\r\nnd Michael James\n&gt; \n&gt; Guru Vachaka Kovai is the biggest collection of Bhaga=\r\nvan=E2=80=99s spoken teachings\n&gt; that was thoroughly checked and revised by=\r\n him during his lifetime. As such\n&gt; it has a unique place in the Ramana lit=\r\nerature.\n&gt; \n&gt; -- \n&gt; ??  ???  ?????  ????  ?????\n&gt; ????????  ????????\n&gt; ????=\r\n?? ????????\n\n\n"}}